### Elasticsearch Infrastructure Tests
### Test Elasticsearch cluster health and basic operations

### 1. Basic Health Check
GET http://localhost:9200
Content-Type: application/json

### 2. Cluster Health
GET http://localhost:9200/_cluster/health
Content-Type: application/json

### 3. Node Information
GET http://localhost:9200/_nodes/_local
Content-Type: application/json

### 4. Create Test Index
PUT http://localhost:9200/test-index
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "settings": {
    "number_of_shards": 1,
    "number_of_replicas": 0
  }
}

### 5. Index Test Document
POST http://localhost:9200/test-index/_doc/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Test LEGO Set",
  "description": "A test document for infrastructure verification",
  "pieces": 100,
  "tags": ["test", "infrastructure"]
}

### 6. Search Test Documents
GET http://localhost:9200/test-index/_search
Content-Type: application/json

### 7. Full-text Search Test
GET http://localhost:9200/test-index/_search?q=LEGO
Content-Type: application/json

### 8. Delete Test Index (cleanup)
DELETE http://localhost:9200/test-index
Content-Type: application/json

### 9. Indices Status
GET http://localhost:9200/_cat/indices?v
Content-Type: application/json

### Expected Results:
# 1. Should return Elasticsearch version and cluster info
# 2. Should return "status": "yellow" or "green" 
# 3. Should return node details
# 4-8. Should demonstrate CRUD operations work
# 9. Should list all indices
